This Privacy Policy sets out details of the Personal Information that Chelsea Football Club collects from you and how we use it, and how to contact us if you have any questions about your Personal Information.
PRIVACY POLICY
Summary
Chelsea FC uses your personal data to allow you to use the features in our content, to administer your online and offline relationships with us, to manage the safety and security of our events and venues, to assess our engagement with our fans and offer them enhanced services and marketing, to comply with our legal obligations and to provide you with Chelsea products, services and other offerings. Some of this information will be provided by you, and others will be generated by Chelsea or provided by third parties.
Our websites may provide interactive features that engage with social media sites, such as Facebook, Instagram and X. If you use these features, these sites will send us personal data about you.
We use cookies and other tracking technologies to personalise content and advertising and to make our content function better. More details of this are set out in our
cookie policy
.
Where we rely on your consent, such as for some direct marketing purposes, or to place cookies, you can withdraw this consent at any time.
Our privacy policy sets out more details of this processing, including details of your data protection rights, including your right to object to certain processing.
1 - INTRODUCTION
Chelsea FC Holdings Limited and our affiliated and associated companies (see section 12 ‘
Which Chelsea FC entity is my controller?’
for more information) (together “
Chelsea FC
”, “
we
” or “
us
”) are committed to safeguarding your personal data and your data privacy rights.
For the purpose of the applicable data protection legislation (including the EU General Data Protection Regulation “
GDPR
”, the Data Protection Act 2018 and the
UK GDPR
), the controller for your personal data will depend on the way in which we interact with you. You can find out more on the specific Chelsea FC entity that is the controller for your processing later in this privacy policy (“
Privacy Policy
”)
This Privacy Policy applies in respect of the personal data we collect, use and process when you use our website
www.chelseafc.com
and any of its related sites (including The Shed and Junior Blues) or use any of our apps (the “
Chelsea FC Sites
”). It also applies to any personal data we collect in your interactions with Chelsea online and offline, including if you visit us at Stamford Bridge, purchase tickets to our games at other venues, enter our competitions, data we may handle if you or your employer supply or partner with Chelsea FC, data collected from applicants as part of job applications and the data we collect and use to send you direct marketing.
This Privacy Policy is not intended to apply to all Chelsea-connected processing. In particular, if you:
are a member of Chelsea FC staff please refer to the Chelsea FC staff privacy policy which has been made available to you;
are an academy player please refer to the academy players privacy policy which has been made available to you;
have made a purchase on
www.chelseamegastore.com
- Chelsea FC’s processing is described in this notice, but the processing of its joint controller Fanatics is described in the Fanatics privacy policy which is available
here
This Privacy Policy should be read alongside our website terms of use, which govern the use of the Chelsea FC Sites, available
here
and our cookies policy available
here
.
This Privacy Policy explains our processing of your personal data, and describes your data protection rights, including the right to object to some of the processing which we carry out. More information about your rights, and how to exercise them, is set out in the “Your Rights” section below.
2 - WHAT PERSONAL DATA DO WE COLLECT?
We will collect your personal data in the following ways:
personal data that you give to us;
personal data that we collect automatically; and
personal data that we receive from third party sources.
Personal data you give to us
We collect personal data from you when you provide it to us directly and through your use of a Chelsea FC Site. This information includes:
Identification and contact information
Name
Age/date of birth
Gender
Email address
Address
Financial Information
Name
Delivery address
Billing address
Email address
Telephone number
Credit/debit card details
Details of your purchases
Marketing and Communications Information
Name
Email address
Date of birth
Country of residence
Marketing preferences
Application-related information
curriculum vitae (CV), cover letter, employment history, education history, qualifications and skills, reference contact information, position preferences, willingness to relocate, desired salary, interests and aspirations, background screening information if relevant and bank account information if we re-imburse expenses
immigration status and information about your entitlement to work
Special Category and Criminal Offence Data
Health or disability related information (e.g. for accessible ticketing)
Religion (e.g. as part of dietary requirements)
Criminal Offence Data (e.g. where we enforce football banning orders or investigate alleged criminal conduct at our venues)
Equal opportunities monitoring information, including information about your ethnic origin, sexual orientation and religion or belief
Additional information you choose to tell us
Information you may add to a Chelsea FC Site profile or post or chat message on a Chelsea FC Site
Information you may provide when you contact us, such as through contacting our customer service team or interacting with us on social media
Information you provide us with when you enter a competition or participate in a survey
Your location
Personal data that we collect automatically
We collect certain information automatically, using cookies and other tracking technologies (you can read our cookies policy
here
), this includes:
IP address
Location information
Usage information (for example the date, times and frequency you access Chelsea FC Sites)
User choices (for example marketing preferences)
Device information when you install and use Chelsea FC Sites
CCTV footage
Personal data that we receive from third party sources
We also receive personal data related to you from third parties, in particular:
third parties who sell match, tour and event tickets for us, including your name, email address and date of birth;
third parties who may have engaged with us to organize an event or to purchase tickets, particularly where they are submitted information about who is attending and any medical assistance or adjustments they may need;
one of our Commercial Partners (see section 5 ‘
Chelsea FC Partners Programme
’ below for more information) for example your name, email address and location;
social media platforms, both where you allow such platforms to share data with use and where you have registered for an account with us using your social media account for example your social media profile name and profile picture;
other sports bodies, including Premier League football clubs, who share information with us as part of integrity and criminal prevention activities. For example, we may receive names, credit/debit card details and contact details for suspected ticket tout purchasers and CCTV or photos of ticket touting on match days, or details of fans identified at away games who are alleged to have shown improper conduct;
data enrichment providers and demographics provider, who may provide information about you to help us better understand you and the products and services most relevant to you;
your employer, where you work for one of Chelsea FC’s suppliers or partners, including information on your role;
members of the public or other users of Chelsea FC Sites, where there are concerns raised about your conduct on a Chelsea FC Site or at our venues or elsewhere that is brought to our attention;
market researchers, where we engage third-party market research agencies to carry out surveys and research into our visitors and fans, and
law enforcement, government, other authorities, sports stakeholders and security providers for the purposes of security or other investigatory activities. For example, we may receive names and CCTV or photos of individuals for public order purposes or the prevention of crime.
3 - HOW AND WHY WE PROCESS YOUR PERSONAL DATA AND OUR LEGAL BASIS FOR PROCESSING
The table below sets out:
our purpose for processing your personal data;
