There are instances where we have a legitimate interest to use your data. Our legitimate interest will vary depending on what we are using your data for, and we explain above what the interest is and how it relates to the processing operations that we are carrying out. Where we process personal data on the basis of a legitimate interest, then – where required by data protection law – we have carried out a balancing test to document our interests, to consider what the impact of the processing will be on individuals and to determine whether individuals interests outweigh our interests in the processing taking place. You can obtain more information about this balancing test by using the contact details at the end of the notice.
Marketing
Depending on your marketing preferences, Chelsea FC, may use your personal data to send you marketing messages by email, phone, SMS or post, or to use targeting cookies to show you relevant ads. Some of these messages may be tailored to you, based on your online profile, your previous browsing or purchase activity, and other information we hold about you.
If you no longer want to receive marketing communications from us or would like to opt back in, you can change your preferences at any time by contacting us via any of the methods given at section 11 ‘
Contact Us
’ below, or by using the ‘unsubscribe’ mechanism in the promotional message or updating your contact preferences in your Chelsea FC Site account. If you unsubscribe from marketing, please note we may still contact you with service messages from time to time (e.g. ticket confirmations, and information about your legal rights). Once you unsubscribe, you may continue to receive marketing messages for a few days while we action your unsubscribe request.
Social Media Marketing
You may also see adverts for Chelsea FC on third party websites, including on social media. These ads may be tailored to you using cookies (which track your web activity, so enable us to serve ads to customers who have visited the Chelsea FC Sites). Where you see an ad on social media, this may be because we have engaged the social network to show adverts to our customers, or users who match the demographic profile of our customers. In some cases, this may involve sharing your email address, cookie data or other personal data with the social network to help create relevant marketing lists. More detail on this is set out in the table above.
Data Enrichment
We carry out data enrichment, demographic data and customer profiling to help us understand your interests and preferences so that we can improve the products and services we offer you. We use FrescoData as one of our data enrichment providers. Data enrichment providers obtain personal data about you either from publicly available sources or third parties who share your personal data with your consent. This personal data is then matched against the personal data we hold. Data enrichment providers will not keep the personal data we share or share it with other third parties.
When using data enrichment service providers we ensure that all our actions comply with applicable data protection legislation. You can access FrescoData’s privacy policy by visiting
https://www.frescodata.com/privacy-policy/
You have the right to opt out of data enrichment or profiling at any time, see section 9 ‘
Your Rights
’ for more information about your rights or contact us via any of the methods given at section 11 ‘
Contact Us
’.
