5 - Chelsea FC commercial Partner programme
We team up with a selection of carefully chosen commercial partners as part of our Commercial Partners programme. A list of our current commercial partners can be found at
www.chelseafc.com/partners
. This list will be updated regularly. Our Commercial Partners programme includes partners from a variety of sectors and is designed to support Chelsea FC and also to bring customers, fans and Chelsea FC Site users a range of our associated and branded offers. If you have given your consent, we may contact you (including by post, phone, SMS or email) in order to tell you more about the offers available to you and about a range of other initiatives from us and on behalf of our Commercial Partners.
6 - Where we transfer your personal data
Our servers are located in the United Kingdom. However, Chelsea FC uses service providers based around the world. Consequently, your personal data may be processed in countries outside of the UK and the Europe Economic Area (EEA). If we transfer personal data outside the UK or the EEA to countries not deemed to offer an adequate level of protection as that of the UK or the EEA, we will, as required by applicable law, ensure that your privacy rights are adequately protected by appropriate safeguards. These safeguards may include standard contractual clauses approved in accordance with the GDPR and/or UK GDPR as applicable, or data bridges approved by relevant authorities, such as the EU-US and UK-US Data Protection Framework.
A copy of relevant safeguards can be obtained for your review on request by using the contact details below. In some cases, we may not require a safeguard to transfer your personal data, for example where transferring your data may be necessary to provide a service you have requested.
7 - How long do we keep your personal data
We will keep your Personal Information for as long as we need it for the purposes set out above, and this period varies depending on the nature of the data and the purpose for which we process it. When we no longer have a need to keep your personal data, we delete or anonymise the relevant personal data.
Data relating to a contract with you
We may need to retain certain personal data in order to provide goods and services to you. For example, if you purchase a ticket or merchandise from us, we will keep a keep a record of your purchase for the period necessary for invoicing, tax and warranty purposes. Where we have a contract with you, such as where you make a purchase or enter a competition we may keep your personal data for up to 6 years after the expiry of our contract.
Automatically collected data
We may retain automatically collected data, for operational needs. For example, to resolve issues with Chelsea FC Sites. Details of the lifespan of our cookies are set out in our cookie policy.
Managing our legal risks or to comply with our legal obligations
We may retain your personal information for as long as necessary to protect our legal interests, such as where:
personal data is relevant to ongoing litigation or a dispute;
you make a request or a complaint we will generally retain correspondence relating to the request or complaint for as long as there remains a potential for litigation or as long as you retain a relationship with Chelsea FC;
we need to for issues relating to safety and security or to investigate suspected unlawful activity;
legislation requires use to retain personal data for a specified period, such as health and safety legislation; or
we receive a legal request such as court order or search warrant.
Marketing
Where we process personal data for marketing purposes or with your consent, we process the data until you ask us to stop and for a short period after this (to allow us to implement your requests).
Please note that where you unsubscribe from our marketing communications, we will keep a record of your email address and/or phone number (as applicable) for suppression purposes to ensure we do not send you marketing emails in future.
CCTV
Where we process CCTV footage, we hold this for 31 days, unless we have been asked to extract footage, in which case this is held for as long as necessary for the reason it has been extracted.
8 - Your rights
You have the right to ask us for a copy of your personal data; to correct, delete or restrict (stop any active) processing of your personal data; to obtain the personal data you provide to us for a contract or with your consent in a structured, machine-readable format; and to ask us for any additional data we may be processing under legitimate interests.
In addition, you can object to the processing of your personal data in some circumstances (in particular, where we don’t have to process the data to meet a contractual or other legal requirement, or where we are using the data for direct marketing).
These rights may be limited, for example if fulfilling your request would reveal personal data about another person, or if you ask us to delete information which we are required by law, permitted by contract or have compelling legitimate interests to keep.
If you wish to exercise any of these rights, including your right to delete an account on a Chelsea FC Site or app, please contact us at the contact details set out below. In some cases, you may also be able to exercise these rights directly by making changes through your account, or following the instructions or link sent in an electronic message.
We hope to be able to address any complaints or concerns you have relating to our processing of your data. However, if you have unresolved concerns, you have the right to complain to a data protection authority in the country that you reside in or, the country of your place of work or the country where the alleged infringement took place. This is likely to be the Information Commissioner’s Office, whose contact details can be found at www.ico.org.uk.
Data that is mandatory is indicated on relevant forms that you complete. Where provision of data is mandatory, if relevant data is not provided, then we will not be able to fulfil your requests to register, make a purchase or otherwise engage with us. All other provision of your information is optional.
9 - Children
Chelsea FC Sites are not intended for users under 13 years old. Users under 13 should visit the
Junior Blues site
, our site designed especially for younger children. We recommend that parents supervise their children while they are online. There are various control tools available for online services that we advise parents to utilise in order to create a child-friendly online environment for their children.
We are dedicated to the protection of children's personal data and we do not actively market to children under the age of 13. We endeavour to limit the amount of personal data which we collect from users who are under 13. Users who are under 13 must always ask their parent or guardian for permission before you:
set up an account on the Junior Blues site;
email us, or ask us to email anything to you/another user under 13;
send any information to us;
enter any competition or game that requires information about you/another user under 13 or offers a prize;
post any information on any bulletin board or enter any chat room; or
offer to agree to buy anything online.
