11 - Changes to our policy
In order to comply with the law and to meet our changing business requirements, our policies and procedures are constantly under review. From time to time, we reserve the right to modify, alter or update this Privacy Policy. We will post the revised Privacy Policy on the Chelsea FC Sites, and we will provide you with a new privacy notice when we make any substantial updates. We may also notify you in other ways from time to time about the processing of your personal information.
This Privacy Policy was last updated in February 2025.
12 - Which Chelsea FC Entity is my Controller?
The Chelsea FC Group is made up of the following companies: Chelsea FC Holdings Limited (company number 02536231), Chelsea Football Club Limited (company number 01965149), Chelsea FC Merchandising Limited (company number 02779831), Chelsea Football Club Women Limited (company number 07377729) The Hotel at Chelsea Limited (company number 02737849) and Chelsea Car Parks Limited (company number 03008949). The registered office of each of these entities is Stamford Bridge, Fulham Road, London SW6 1HS.
Different Chelsea FC entities are responsible for various processing set out in this notice. In all cases, you can contact the relevant controller – and ask for confirmation of the relevant controller for certain processing of your data – by contacting us using the contact details set out above.
The controller for any processing of personal data in connection with ticketing or attendance at Stamford Bridge or Kingsmeadow is Chelsea Football Club Limited for men’s team matches and Chelsea Football Club Women Limited for women’s team matches.
The controller for all processing in connection with the Chelsea megastore is Chelsea F.C. Merchandising Limited, together with its joint controller Fanatics who operate the Chelsea online megastore.
The controller for all processing in connection with Chelsea FC Sites is Chelsea FC Holdings Limited.
